    <cite class="fn">Laura</cite><br/>

            <div class="comment-meta-data">

    Published July 13, 2012  2:47 am <span class="meta-sep"></span> <a href="#comment-362" class="permalink" title="Permalink to this comment">Permalink</a> 
            </div>
        <p>I am truly touched by Aaron&#8217;s wish, and by his family&#8217;s determination to make it happen.  I was a young widow with a young child, who chose to celebrate my late husband&#8217;s short, but beautiful life, rather than bury myself in grief over my loss.  Those we have lost are best memorialized by remembering the light they brought to our lives while they were with us, rather than emphasizing the void left in our hearts by their loss.  Tonight I will raise a toast to Aaron, and I will leave a generous tip in his honor.</p>

