        <p>To aaroncollins.org.  I am a tax preparer (enrolled agent). When you give a tip, the receiver MUST pay taxes on it.  Because you are giving this really as a gift, which would not be taxable to the receiver, give the money as a cashier check marked in the Memo section as a gift in memory of Aaron Collins.  The receiver would not have to pay taxes on it although if the trust paid out over a certain amount (currently $2,000,000) they would have to pay taxes on all the gifts.</p>

