        <p>To Aaron and his family: Angels do exist; what you are doing is simply incredible and so caring towards others.  What touches me most is to see a simple young man with a simple salary make such a generous gesture, when people with riches do nothing.  I fell on this post by pure chance, after coming back from helping a friend with 3 children with buying food, when we nearly have nothing in our own fridge.  Meanwhile, I wake up this morning, with a sense of having helped a friend in need.  I am used to giving away my last cent &#8211; as they say &#8211; and have been doing so for years towards the homeless in Montreal.  Aaron is an angel and so is his family for continuing his legacy.</p>

