            <div class="comment-meta-data">

    Published July 25, 2012  1:02 pm <span class="meta-sep"></span> <a href="#comment-1110" class="permalink" title="Permalink to this comment">Permalink</a> 
            </div>
        <p>Thank you for this, Kevin. It deeply touches my heart. Thank YOU for sharing our grief with us. It is a great comfort to us. This morning a friend sent the following poem to me. Aaron helped us to do what this poem says to do.</p>
<p>If I should die and leave you here awhile,<br />
Be not like others, sore and undone,<br />
Who keep long vigils by the silent dust, and weep.<br />
For my sake – turn again to life and smile<br />
Nerving thy heart and trembling hand to do<br />
Something to comfort other hearts than thine.<br />
Complete those dear unfinished tasks of mine<br />
And I, perchance, may therein comfort you.</p>
<p>&#8211;A. Price Hughes &amp; Mary Lee Hall</p>

